            \ for smart letter. Indicate that if this document file is a smart letter.\
            \                        <br/>\"application/vnd.ch.klara.epost.v1+simple_short_message\"\
            \ for simple short message. To send simple short message, leave the document\
            \ type empty.                        <br/>\"application/vnd.ch.klara.epost.v1+incamail\"\
            \ Please use SecureSend instead of IncaMail.                        <br/>\"\
            application/vnd.ch.klara.epost.v1+securesend\" for SecureSend.\t\t\t\t\
            \t\t <br/>null for Physical delivery."
          type: string
          example: application/vnd.ch.klara.epost.smartletter.v1+json
        deliveryChannelPreferences:
          description: "This value defines your preference & priority among delivery\
            \ channels. It defines that your letter/message/document should be delivered\
            \ via which one of the available channels. You can input more than one\
            \ delivery channel. <br><br>\nThe order of delivery channels defines the\
            \ priority of each channel. Meaning, at first we try to deliver via the\
            \ first mentioned delivery channel, if it's unsuccessful, we would try\
            \ via the second channel mentioned, and so on. <br><br>\nIf delivery is\
            \ not successful via any of the delivery methods, then an error response\
            \ will be returned to the sender.<br><br>\n<b>DIGITAL</b> delivering it\
            \ to the recipient's ePost letterbox (available for all types of documents/letters/messages)<br>\n\
            <b>PHYSICAL</b> printing and sending the letter physically (only specific\
            \ pdf formats are accepted)<br>\n<b>SMS</b> delivering the \"simple short\
            \ message\" as a SMS to the recipient's mobile phone. (only for simple\
            \ short message media type)<br>\n<b>EBILL</b> delivering it to the recipient's\
            \ eBill (available for invoice document type with pdf format)<br>\n<b>EMAIL</b>\
            \ delivering it to the recipient who using email<br>\n<b>AUTO</b> will\
