      description: "The channel we will use to contact the recipient with the request\
        \ to onboard to ePost. Currently, only EMAIL is supported."
      enum:
      - EMAIL
      type: string
    forcedOnboarding:
      description: |-
        This object is optional. Defines whether all recipients of this document should be forced to register to ePost in order to receive this document. If the recipient is already registered to ePost, the normal delivery flow applies. If the recipient is not yet registered to ePost, we will send him an email asking him to register to ePost in order to receive the document. The document is stored for up to 60 days and will be delivered to the recipient as soon as he registers to ePost. After 60 days the delivery will expire.
        Reminder emails are sent to the recipient after 2, 25, 40 and 55 days.
        Forced onboarding is only available for the delivery channel DIGITAL. Additionally the unhashed credential EMAIL is required for forced onboarding (onboarding request email will be sent to this email address) and the minimum level of trust must be BRONZE.
      type: object
      properties:
        channel:
          allOf:
          - $ref: '#/components/schemas/channel'
          - description: "The channel we will use to contact the recipient with the\
              \ request to onboard to ePost. Currently, only EMAIL is supported."
            example: EMAIL
            writeOnly: true
        language:
          allOf:
          - $ref: '#/components/schemas/language'
          - description: Language of the recipient. Defines the language we will use
              in the email we send to the recipient with the request to onboard to
              ePost.
            example: EN
            writeOnly: true
        emailToBeInformedWhenExpired:
          description: "This email address is used to inform the sender, in case the\
            \ forced onboarding eLetter expires after 60 days (recipient didn't register)\
            \ or should an error occur in the delivery of the forced onboarding eLetter."
          type: string
          example: peter.muster@gmail.com
    language:
      description: Language of the recipient. Defines the language we will use in
        the email we send to the recipient with the request to onboard to ePost.
      enum:
      - EN
      - DE
      - FR
      - IT
      type: string
